Yeah I do hate your guts, but I
sure like the bag they come in.

1128
01:05:50,012 --> 01:05:53,289
Come on, lets eat.

1129
01:05:56,018 --> 01:05:58,123
I understand about Ma 17

1130
01:05:58,187 --> 01:06:00,827
and some of the rest, but then
there is the bible stuff.

1131
01:06:00,890 --> 01:06:02,198
The "prepare to meet
your maker",

1132
01:06:02,258 --> 01:06:03,703
you never know when
your number is up.

1133
01:06:03,759 --> 01:06:05,329
Don't have regrets.

1134
01:06:05,394 --> 01:06:06,998
The ecclesiastes
thing makes sense...

1135
01:06:07,063 --> 01:06:09,373
yep, eat drink and be merry.

1136
01:06:09,432 --> 01:06:10,877
I'm all for that.

1137
01:06:10,933 --> 01:06:12,571
It's very optimistic.

1138
01:06:12,635 --> 01:06:14,410
It is not.

1139
01:06:14,470 --> 01:06:16,780
I'm prepared, and you just
keep your fingers crossed.

1140
01:06:16,839 --> 01:06:19,080
You think the parrot
makes sense,

1141
01:06:19,141 --> 01:06:21,849
but there are some things you
are never going to learn.

1142
01:06:21,911 --> 01:06:23,754
You don't understand life
like I don't understand

1143
01:06:23,813 --> 01:06:25,952
how to fix a car.

1144
01:06:26,015 --> 01:06:28,154
It's all just one big
tangle under the hood.

1145
01:06:28,217 --> 01:06:29,855
I think some women
believe that a man is born

1146
01:06:29,919 --> 01:06:31,626
the moment they meet him.

1147
01:06:31,687 --> 01:06:35,362
Now what'll you you have?

1148
01:06:37,093 --> 01:06:39,937
Why thank you, Lyman.

1149
01:06:39,996 --> 01:06:43,910
"T builder of men."

1150
01:06:43,966 --> 01:06:48,415
well, I do my best.

1151
01:06:50,406 --> 01:06:51,851
Margie, this is Fiona.

1152
01:06:51,907 --> 01:06:54,114
I heard about you.

1153
01:06:54,176 --> 01:06:56,884
Is my Lyman sweet
on you, honey?

1154
01:06:56,946 --> 01:06:59,051
I think it's the
way that I dress.

1155
01:06:59,115 --> 01:07:01,561
Thank you Lyman,
for bringing her by.

1156
01:07:01,617 --> 01:07:03,893
I approve.

1157
01:07:03,953 --> 01:07:05,955
MARGIE VO: They were
talking so hard,

1158
01:07:06,022 --> 01:07:07,626
like there was a
fire somewhere and

1159
01:07:07,690 --> 01:07:09,863
only their words
could put it out.

1160
01:07:09,925 --> 01:07:12,269
I could tell just by the sound,

1161
01:07:12,328 --> 01:07:17,505
seemed like Lyman was finally
getting closer to an answer.

1162
01:07:17,566 --> 01:07:19,409
I left them alone.

1163
01:07:19,468 --> 01:07:23,348
I decided dinner
was on me that night.

1164
01:07:29,712 --> 01:07:31,419
How many campbells
have you called?

1165
01:07:31,480 --> 01:07:34,086
I'm still trying.
I have dozens left.

1166
01:07:34,150 --> 01:07:35,720
Some of these people just talk
and talk and talk, and

1167
01:07:35,785 --> 01:07:39,323
I can't get them off the phone.

1168
01:07:39,388 --> 01:07:41,868
What?

1169
01:07:41,924 --> 01:07:44,495
Cheese stuck on your teeth.

1170
01:07:49,098 --> 01:07:53,706
Toast crumbs at the
corners of your mouth.

1171
01:07:53,769 --> 01:07:57,546
Butter on your lips.

1172
01:08:00,643 --> 01:08:02,782
Want to go fishing?

1173
01:08:02,845 --> 01:08:06,019
Oh Lyman, you say
the sweetest things.

1174
01:08:10,186 --> 01:08:13,463
It takes a few seconds to reach
bottom, but it comes up quick.

1175
01:08:16,826 --> 01:08:21,468
I've found hubcaps, cans, tools.

1176
01:08:21,530 --> 01:08:24,739
Once I found a set of
braces, with a tooth in it.

1177
01:08:24,800 --> 01:08:28,145
Wow Lyman, that's the mother
load. Now we can retire,

1178
01:08:28,204 --> 01:08:33,313
and live happily ever after.

1179
01:08:33,375 --> 01:08:36,015
Maybe one day I'll solve
a great mystery.

1180
01:08:36,078 --> 01:08:38,058
The crime of the century.

1181
01:08:38,114 --> 01:08:41,425
Until then I just
fish for clues.

1182
01:08:48,824 --> 01:08:50,424
Fiona?

1183
01:08:54,029 --> 01:08:57,943
Happy birthday... Mr. Lyman.

1184
01:08:58,000 --> 01:09:00,241
What?

1185
01:09:00,302 --> 01:09:05,718
I couldn't bear the thought of
you never having birthdays.

1186
01:09:06,775 --> 01:09:08,584
But I don't know
what the date is.

1187
01:09:08,644 --> 01:09:10,146
So I figured someone
better pick a date,

1188
01:09:10,212 --> 01:09:11,919
and I say it's today.

1189
01:09:11,981 --> 01:09:14,291
Unless you can prove me wrong.

1190
01:09:14,350 --> 01:09:16,762
I declare this the
thirty something

1191
01:09:16,819 --> 01:09:20,323
birthday of baby boy Lyman.

1192
01:09:22,992 --> 01:09:24,699
It's around now that
you blow out the candle

1193
01:09:24,760 --> 01:09:29,266
before I'm horribly
disfigured by molten wax?

1194
01:09:32,735 --> 01:09:37,047
There. You're no longer a
birthday cake virgin.

1195
01:10:00,829 --> 01:10:03,105
If you're looking for
something french and lacy,

1196
01:10:03,165 --> 01:10:07,978
you uh... you
got the wrong girl.

1197
01:10:08,037 --> 01:10:10,847
I uh... I don't think
I'll be talking anymore

1198
01:10:10,906 --> 01:10:12,408
from here on out.

1199
01:10:30,793 --> 01:10:32,393
[d...]

1200
01:10:46,809 --> 01:10:48,618
You're perfect...

1201
01:10:48,677 --> 01:10:51,783
Sshhhhhh...

1202
01:10:54,883 --> 01:10:56,226
[car screeching]

1203
01:10:56,285 --> 01:10:59,027
[dog squealing]

1204
01:10:59,088 --> 01:11:02,968
What was that?

1205
01:11:03,025 --> 01:11:06,063
They hit a goddamn dog.

1206
01:11:07,529 --> 01:11:10,703
Stay here.

1207
01:11:10,766 --> 01:11:14,304
[whimpering]

1208
01:11:22,911 --> 01:11:26,085
Is it going to be okay?

1209
01:11:26,148 --> 01:11:28,219
Lyman?

1210
01:11:28,284 --> 01:11:30,696
What are you doing?

1211
01:11:30,753 --> 01:11:33,063
Oh god, please no.

1212
01:11:33,122 --> 01:11:34,601
Just stay in the truck, Fiona!

1213
01:11:34,657 --> 01:11:37,536
Lyman, we can take
it to the vet.

1214
01:11:37,593 --> 01:11:41,632
Lyman, please listen to me!

1215
01:11:41,697 --> 01:11:44,644
Lyman, please!

1216
01:11:44,700 --> 01:11:47,010
Lyman, no!

1217
01:11:47,069 --> 01:11:49,606
[gunshot]

1218
01:11:49,672 --> 01:11:54,382
[crying]

1219
01:12:42,624 --> 01:12:45,730
Fiona, there was no saving it.

1220
01:12:48,397 --> 01:12:52,174
How can you bear to do this?

1221
01:12:54,803 --> 01:12:59,582
I've never had to
share it with anyone.

1222
01:13:01,910 --> 01:13:05,756
I don't want to share that.

1223
01:13:45,821 --> 01:13:47,926
[chirping]

1224
01:13:53,228 --> 01:13:56,402
Give some to the parrot.

1225
01:14:01,003 --> 01:14:03,506
Just you and me now, buddy.

1226
01:14:03,572 --> 01:14:07,281
From now on,
thou shalt be called...

1227
01:14:07,342 --> 01:14:10,221
"zane".

1228
01:14:10,279 --> 01:14:13,351
[chirping]

1229
01:14:16,218 --> 01:14:20,166
[phone ringing]

1230
01:14:20,222 --> 01:14:21,701
Hello?

1231
01:14:21,757 --> 01:14:23,100
MRS. WEBER: Hello?

1232
01:14:23,158 --> 01:14:24,136
Can I speak to Mr.
Lyman please?

1233
01:14:24,193 --> 01:14:25,365
Speaking.

1234
01:14:25,427 --> 01:14:26,804
This is mrs. Weber.

1235
01:14:26,862 --> 01:14:29,741
I'm returning your
call about the parrot.

1236
01:14:30,833 --> 01:14:32,278
Come on in,

1237
01:14:32,334 --> 01:14:33,608
one more won't make
a difference.

1238
01:14:33,669 --> 01:14:35,876
WEBER: Jesus Christ,
it's him.

1239
01:14:35,938 --> 01:14:37,918
I don't believe it,
he's still alive.

1240
01:14:37,973 --> 01:14:39,350
Yep.

1241
01:14:39,408 --> 01:14:41,319
That awful bird.

1242
01:14:41,376 --> 01:14:44,255
Mr. Lyman, this is
my husband duncan.

1243
01:14:44,313 --> 01:14:46,315
[chirping]

1244
01:14:46,381 --> 01:14:48,383
Oh, he's a sight for sore eyes.

1245
01:14:48,450 --> 01:14:51,863
Kids, this is old tonto.

1246
01:14:51,920 --> 01:14:54,901
My dear friend from back
in the olden days

1247
01:14:54,957 --> 01:14:56,459
when I was your age, henry.

1248
01:14:56,525 --> 01:14:58,527
BILLIE: I'm Billie.

1249
01:14:58,594 --> 01:15:00,096
Dad always talked about his
parrot like he was human.

1250
01:15:00,162 --> 01:15:01,436
SUSIE: Sue.

1251
01:15:01,497 --> 01:15:02,908
We didn't know what to believe.

1252
01:15:02,965 --> 01:15:05,070
Tonto was my best friend.

1253
01:15:05,133 --> 01:15:11,880
We used to listen to the lone
ranger on the radio every week.

1254
01:15:11,940 --> 01:15:15,080
He could mimic all
of the theme music.

1255
01:15:15,143 --> 01:15:20,889
[sings theme]

1256
01:15:15,143 --> 01:15:17,922
Does he still say
<i>"Hi-ho silver away?"</i>

1257
